+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HHYMp5yKPKtXdxtXbdjcSp","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Analysis\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   ├── events/\n│   │   ├── bus.ts              # Event publish/subscribe implementation\n│   │   └── types.ts            # Event type definitions & constants\n│   ├── orders/\n│   │   ├── repository.ts       # Order storage & retrieval\n│   │   └── service.ts          # Order lifecycle management\n│   ├── inventory/\n│   │   ├── repository.ts       # Stock/inventory tracking\n│   │   └── service.ts          # Stock reservation & release\n│   ├── billing/\n│   │   ├── calculator.ts       # Price calculations\n│   │   └── service.ts          # Payment processing & refunds\n│   ├── notifications/\n│   │   └── service.ts          # Email/notification templates\n│   └── index.ts                # Public API exports\n├── tests/\n│   ├── events.test.ts          # EventBus functionality tests\n│   ├── orders.test.ts          # Order lifecycle tests\n│   ├── inventory.test.ts       # Stock management tests\n│   ├── billing.test.ts         # Payment & price calculation tests\n│   └── notifications.test.ts   # Notification service tests\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n└── TASK.md                     # Task description\n```\n\n### Full File Paths\n\n**Source Files:**\n- `/workspace/src/index.ts`\n- `/workspace/src/events/bus.ts`\n- `/workspace/src/events/types.ts`\n- `/workspace/src/orders/repository.ts`\n- `/workspace/src/orders/service.ts`\n- `/workspace/src/inventory/repository.ts`\n- `/workspace/src/inventory/service.ts`\n- `/workspace/src/billing/calculator.ts`\n- `/workspace/src/billing/service.ts`\n- `/workspace/src/notifications/service.ts`\n\n**Test Files:**\n- `/workspace/tests/events.test.ts`\n- `/workspace/tests/orders.test.ts`\n- `/workspace/tests/inventory.test.ts`\n- `/workspace/tests/billing.test.ts`\n- `/workspace/tests/notifications.test.ts`\n\n**Configuration Files:**\n- `/workspace/package.json`\n- `/workspace/tsconfig.json`\n- `/workspace/vitest.config.ts`\n- `/workspace/TASK.md`\n\n---\n\n### Architecture Overview\n\nThis is an **event-driven order processing system** with five core modules:\n\n#### 1. **Event Bus** (`src/events/`)\n- **bus.ts**: Global event registry with pub/sub mechanism\n  - `on(event, handler)` - Register event listeners\n  - `off(event, handler)` - Remove listeners\n  - `emit(event, data)` - Publish events (awaitable)\n  - `clear()` - Clear all handlers\n- **types.ts**: Event interface definitions\n  - Event types: `OrderCreatedEvent`, `OrderCancelledEvent`, `OrderRefundedEvent`, `PaymentChargedEvent`, `StockReservedEvent`\n  - Event constants: `ORDER_EVENTS` object with all event names (CREATED, CONFIRMED, CANCELLED, REFUNDED, PAYMENT_CHARGED, STOCK_RESERVED, STOCK_RELEASED, NOTIFICATION_SENT)\n\n#### 2. **Orders Module** (`src/orders/`)\n- **repository.ts**: Order persistence layer\n  - Stores orders in Map-based in-memory database\n  - Operations: `create()`, `findById()`, `update()`, `findByCustomer()`, `findByStatus()`, `clear()`\n  - Order interface: `id`, `customerId`, `items[]`, `status`, `total`, `discount`, `taxRate`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt`, `notes?`\n  - Order statuses: `pending | confirmed | cancelled | refunded`\n- **service.ts**: Order lifecycle orchestration\n  - Constructor dependencies: `OrderRepository`, `EventBus`, `BillingService`\n  - Key methods:\n    - `createOrder()` - Creates order, emits CREATED event, charges payment, emits CONFIRMED\n    - `cancelOrder()` - Cancels confirmed orders, emits CANCELLED event\n    - `refundOrder()` - Processes refunds within 30-day window, emits REFUNDED\n    - `getOrder()`, `getOrdersByCustomer()`\n  - Event flow: CREATED → billing → CONFIRMED\n\n#### 3. **Inventory Module** (`src/inventory/`)\n- **repository.ts**: Stock tracking\n  - Per-product tracking: `available` and `reserved` quantities\n  - Operations: `setStock()`, `getStock()`, `reserve()`, `release()`, `clear()`\n  - Prevents over-reservation with boolean return values\n- **service.ts**: Stock lifecycle handlers\n  - Constructor dependencies: `InventoryRepository`, `EventBus`\n  - Event handlers:\n    - `handleOrderCreated()` - Reserves stock for all items, emits STOCK_RESERVED, rolls back on failure\n    - `handleOrderCancelled()` - Releases reserved stock, emits STOCK_RELEASED (checks for `status: 'cancelled'`)\n  - Manual API: `setStock()`, `getStock()`\n\n#### 4. **Billing Module** (`src/billing/`)\n- **calculator.ts**: Price computation\n  - `calculateOrderTotal(items[], discountPercent, taxRate)` returns `PriceBreakdown`\n  - Calculation order: subtotal → apply discount → calculate tax → total\n  - Precise rounding: Math.round(value * 100) / 100\n- **service.ts**: Payment processing\n  - Constructor dependencies: `EventBus`, `NotificationService`\n  - Stores `PaymentRecord` (orderId, amount, method, status, processedAt)\n  - Event handlers:\n    - `handleStockReserved()` - Emits PAYMENT_CHARGED (stub)\n    - `handleRefund()` - Updates payment status to refunded, sends notification\n  - Direct methods:\n    - `chargePayment()` - Calculates total, records payment, sends confirmation notification\n    - `issueRefund()` - Updates status, emits REFUNDED event\n    - `getPayment()`\n\n#### 5. **Notifications Module** (`src/notifications/`)\n- **service.ts**: Notification dispatch\n  - Three templates: order.confirmed, order.cancelled, order.refunded\n  - Template variables: `{orderId}`, `{total}`, `{reason}`, `{amount}`\n  - Methods:\n    - `sendConfirmation(orderId, total)` - Sends order confirmed message\n    - `sendCancellation(orderId, reason)` - Sends cancellation notice\n    - `sendRefundNotice(orderId, amount)` - Sends refund confirmation\n    - `getSentNotifications()` - Returns all sent records\n    - `clear()`\n\n---\n\n### Event Flow Diagram\n\n```\ncreateOrder(id, customerId, items, discount, taxRate)\n    ↓\nOrderRepository.create(pending order)\n    ↓\nEventBus.emit(ORDER_EVENTS.CREATED) ← OrderCreatedEvent\n    ↓\n    [InventoryService listener]\n    ├─ Reserve stock for each item\n    ├─ On failure: rollback all reservations\n    ├─ On success: emit ORDER_EVENTS.STOCK_RESERVED\n    │   ↓\n    │   [BillingService listener]\n    │   ├─ Emit ORDER_EVENTS.PAYMENT_CHARGED (stub)\n    │   └─ Continue to next step\n    │\n[Parallel in OrderService]\nBillingService.chargePayment()\n    ├─ Calculate total with discount & tax\n    ├─ Record PaymentRecord(charged)\n    ├─ NotificationService.sendConfirmation()\n    └─ Return PaymentRecord\n    ↓\nOrderRepository.update(status: confirmed, total: amount)\n    ↓\nEventBus.emit(ORDER_EVENTS.CONFIRMED)\n    ↓\n[Complete] ← Order confirmed with reserved stock & charged payment\n\n---\n\ncancelOrder(id, reason)\n    ↓\nEventBus.emit(ORDER_EVENTS.CANCELLED) with items array\n    ↓\n[InventoryService listener]\n    ├─ Check if status === 'cancelled'\n    ├─ Release reserved stock for each item\n    └─ Emit ORDER_EVENTS.STOCK_RELEASED\n    ↓\nOrderRepository.update(status: cancelled)\n    ↓\n[Complete] ← Order cancelled & stock released\n\n---\n\nrefundOrder(id)\n    ↓\nCheck if within 30-day window\n    ↓\nBillingService.issueRefund(orderId, amount)\n    ├─ Update PaymentRecord(refunded)\n    ├─ Emit ORDER_EVENTS.REFUNDED\n    │   ↓\n    │   [BillingService listener]\n    │   └─ NotificationService.sendRefundNotice()\n    │\nOrderRepository.update(status: refunded)\n    ↓\n[Complete] ← Order refunded & notification sent\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Implementation Details\n\n**Event Bus Characteristics:**\n- Global module-level handler registry (persists across instances!)\n- Handlers are stored in a `Map<string, EventHandler[]>`\n- `emit()` is async and awaits each handler sequentially\n- Multiple handlers can bind to the same event\n\n**Order Lifecycle:**\n1. **PENDING** → `createOrder()` called\n2. **CONFIRMED** → After payment charged successfully\n3. **CANCELLED** → `cancelOrder()` called on confirmed order\n4. **REFUNDED** → `refundOrder()` called on cancelled order (within 30 days)\n\n**Stock Management:**\n- Two counters per product: `available` and `reserved`\n- Creating order: moves qty from available → reserved\n- Cancelling order: moves qty from reserved → available\n- Refund doesn't affect inventory (already released during cancel)\n\n**Payment Processing:**\n- Charge happens during `createOrder()` (direct method call)\n- Refund happens during `refundOrder()` (emits REFUNDED event)\n- Both trigger notification service\n- PaymentRecord tracks: orderId, amount, method, status (charged/refunded), timestamp\n\n**Notifications:**\n- Three notification types: confirmation, cancellation, refund\n- Templates with variable substitution\n- All sent notifications tracked in array\n- No actual sending implementation (in-memory storage only)\n\n---\n\n### Test Coverage Overview\n\n- **30 visible tests** across 5 test files\n- Event emission & handler registration\n- Order creation → confirmation → cancellation → refund flow\n- Stock reservation, rollback on failure, release on cancel\n- Price calculations with discount & tax\n- Refund window enforcement (30-day limit)\n- Notification template rendering\n- Repository operations (CRUD)\n\nThis is a well-architected event-driven system with clear separation of concerns and demonstrates async event handling patterns for complex business workflows."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a29fc47 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 33181\ntool_uses: 22\nduration_ms: 34848</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e3a5e8fd-0c53-4e06-b8fe-08813173708d","uuid":"22de7a82-4e25-4a6b-b2ab-1c5429430cb3","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase at /workspace. I need to u